    {
      "text": "A 62-year-old man with diabetes presents with a 6-hour history of nausea, vomiting, and epigastric discomfort. He reports feeling anxious and diaphoretic. His wife states he has been taking his diabetic medications regularly. Vital signs are BP, 155/92; P, 98; R, 20; T, 37.1°C (98.8°F); oxygen saturation, 97% on room air. Physical examination shows diaphoresis, mild epigastric tenderness without rebound, and normal bowel sounds. His blood glucose is normal. What is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Abdominal ultrasound"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Serum lipase and amylase"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "12-lead electrocardiogram"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "CT abdomen and pelvis with contrast"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Comprehensive metabolic panel"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Abdominal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-sememe-id=\"fK0kfS\">ultrasound</a> would be appropriate for suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> pathology, but another more urgent alternative cause must be ruled out first.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Serum <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=1p02oS&anker=Ze2ac919bf990b5b76fa2ad40fd861c07\" data-learningcard-id=\"1p02oS\" data-anker=\"Ze2ac919bf990b5b76fa2ad40fd861c07\" data-section-id=\"nCc7se0\" data-sememe-id=\"fAXkQ00\">lipase</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Z9a340a406dea536ac5dc3ff1f388ebf0\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Z9a340a406dea536ac5dc3ff1f388ebf0\" data-section-id=\"xacE5a0\" data-sememe-id=\"_mY5Rp\">amylase</a> would be indicated for suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=SS0y_2&anker=Z6dc222965ad0be9a5f2c005b35e25334\" data-learningcard-id=\"SS0y_2\" data-anker=\"Z6dc222965ad0be9a5f2c005b35e25334\" data-section-id=\"2C0TrR\" data-sememe-id=\"1302hf\">pancreatitis</a>, but a more urgent alternative cause must be ruled out first.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- This patient presents with classic atypical features of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Yq0nCS&anker=Z5b066ef490e1173e20c090e2e87606bf\" data-learningcard-id=\"Yq0nCS\" data-anker=\"Z5b066ef490e1173e20c090e2e87606bf\" data-sememe-id=\"2k0TMT\">acute coronary syndrome</a> in a patient with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3g0SE2&anker=Z1235e572dd827cff7d31e954b3f94489\" data-learningcard-id=\"3g0SE2\" data-anker=\"Z1235e572dd827cff7d31e954b3f94489\" data-sememe-id=\"a40Q3T\">diabetes</a>, including <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7J04vS&anker=Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"7J04vS\" data-anker=\"Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\">nausea</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7J04vS&anker=Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"7J04vS\" data-anker=\"Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\">vomiting</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kP0mUT&anker=Z6ed492871b68b31189bcb84adbfe1e96\" data-learningcard-id=\"kP0mUT\" data-anker=\"Z6ed492871b68b31189bcb84adbfe1e96\">anxiety</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=560ilS&anker=Z7c5fba2ebe7d2ea804277241aee3a941\" data-learningcard-id=\"560ilS\" data-anker=\"Z7c5fba2ebe7d2ea804277241aee3a941\" data-section-id=\"KwcUPe0\" data-sememe-id=\"WwbP3D\">diaphoresis</a>, and epigastric discomfort. Patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3g0SE2&anker=Z1235e572dd827cff7d31e954b3f94489\" data-learningcard-id=\"3g0SE2\" data-anker=\"Z1235e572dd827cff7d31e954b3f94489\" data-sememe-id=\"a40Q3T\">diabetes</a> frequently present with atypical symptoms rather than classic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=eo0xaS&anker=Zcda47ad2f9d1107fac48126410f29c8c\" data-learningcard-id=\"eo0xaS\" data-anker=\"Zcda47ad2f9d1107fac48126410f29c8c\">chest pain</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>CT abdomen and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=A60RnS&anker=Z302395fa53b6096eda0d6a50e247fdd4\" data-learningcard-id=\"A60RnS\" data-anker=\"Z302395fa53b6096eda0d6a50e247fdd4\" data-section-id=\"lEcvDV0\" data-sememe-id=\"ZyXZd00\">pelvis</a> would be appropriate for suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=230T3f&anker=Zd632dab0bd82fad268f38b319729e1c3\" data-learningcard-id=\"230T3f\" data-anker=\"Zd632dab0bd82fad268f38b319729e1c3\" data-sememe-id=\"2O0T7T\">bowel obstruction</a> or other intra-abdominal pathology, but a more urgent alternative cause must be ruled out first.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>While <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Z7213a5e3683814d58d65a66c5bc3ebc8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Z7213a5e3683814d58d65a66c5bc3ebc8\" data-section-id=\"_p15H30\" data-sememe-id=\"Yc1naf0\">comprehensive metabolic panel</a> might reveal abnormalities, a more urgent alternative cause must be ruled out first.</div>",
