    {
      "text": "A 32-year-old woman presents with a 4-hour history of nausea and vomiting. She reports diffuse abdominal pain that has progressively worsened, now accompanied by an inability to pass gas or have a bowel movement. Physical examination shows a distended, tympanitic abdomen with hyperactive bowel sounds. Her surgical history includes appendectomy 3 years ago. Vital signs are BP, 115/65; P, 95; R, 22; T, 37.2°C (99.0°F). What is the most appropriate initial diagnostic study?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Upper endoscopy"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Abdominal ultrasound"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "MRI abdomen"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "CT abdomen with IV contrast"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "X-ray abdomen"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=f80kN3&anker=Z1a617ceb3d8b9832108168a091314359\" data-learningcard-id=\"f80kN3\" data-anker=\"Z1a617ceb3d8b9832108168a091314359\" data-sememe-id=\"kj0m0T\">Upper endoscopy</a> is indicated for suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZS0Zy2&anker=Z63797faee8c413c0c066ee4e1af342dc\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZS0Zy2\" data-anker=\"Z63797faee8c413c0c066ee4e1af342dc\" data-section-id=\"uJ1pD30\" data-sememe-id=\"hF0c33\">upper gastrointestinal bleeding</a> or gastroduodenal pathology, not for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=230T3f&anker=Z5e4a226f7c70e803f9637faff41a11cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"230T3f\" data-anker=\"Z5e4a226f7c70e803f9637faff41a11cc\" data-section-id=\"pPaLfk\" data-sememe-id=\"_y053i\">mechanical bowel obstruction</a>. This patient's presentation is consistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=230T3f&anker=Z80f01674fa1ce571e62a8ce74bd34a99\" data-learningcard-id=\"230T3f\" data-anker=\"Z80f01674fa1ce571e62a8ce74bd34a99\" data-section-id=\"pPaLfk\" data-sememe-id=\"5mciT10\">small bowel obstruction</a> rather than upper <span data-sememe-id=\"LBewYYa\">gastrointestinal</span> pathology.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Abdominal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-sememe-id=\"fK0kfS\">ultrasound</a> is used to evaluate <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Q60ukS&anker=Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-learningcard-id=\"Q60ukS\" data-anker=\"Zfbd83f7912051272d7b56a91f4568354\" data-section-id=\"eFcxSV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5SXiZB\">gallbladder</a> pathology and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=A60RnS&anker=Z302395fa53b6096eda0d6a50e247fdd4\" data-learningcard-id=\"A60RnS\" data-anker=\"Z302395fa53b6096eda0d6a50e247fdd4\" data-section-id=\"lEcvDV0\" data-sememe-id=\"ZyXZd00\">pelvic</a> conditions but is not the initial imaging modality of choice for suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=230T3f&anker=Zd632dab0bd82fad268f38b319729e1c3\" data-learningcard-id=\"230T3f\" data-anker=\"Zd632dab0bd82fad268f38b319729e1c3\" data-sememe-id=\"2O0T7T\">bowel obstruction</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-sememe-id=\"fK0kfS\">Ultrasound</a> has limited ability to visualize bowel loops and identify obstruction patterns.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pN0LXg&anker=Zefb6206a3f821bf7e5942b654dc6f6cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"pN0LXg\" data-anker=\"Zefb6206a3f821bf7e5942b654dc6f6cf\" data-sememe-id=\"8n0OEg\">MRI</a> abdomen may be considered in patients with contraindications to radiation exposure such as pregnant patients, but it is not the initial imaging study for suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=230T3f&anker=Zd632dab0bd82fad268f38b319729e1c3\" data-learningcard-id=\"230T3f\" data-anker=\"Zd632dab0bd82fad268f38b319729e1c3\" data-sememe-id=\"2O0T7T\">bowel obstruction</a> in a hemodynamically stable patient.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- This patient has <span class=\"linksuggest\"><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=230T3f&anker=Z2411c29e96bbcd139c9f3329c140a348\" data-learningcard-id=\"230T3f\" data-anker=\"Z2411c29e96bbcd139c9f3329c140a348\" data-section-id=\"7Pa4Tk\" data-sememe-id=\"vuWAGM0\">clinical features of bowel obstruction</a></span>. CT abdomen with IV contrast is highly sensitive for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=230T3f&anker=Z5e4a226f7c70e803f9637faff41a11cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"230T3f\" data-anker=\"Z5e4a226f7c70e803f9637faff41a11cc\" data-section-id=\"pPaLfk\" data-sememe-id=\"_y053i\">mechanical bowel obstruction</a> and can help identify the transition point.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"BDczge0\">X-ray abdomen</span> would be the appropriate initial test in a <span data-sememe-id=\"3LdSxq0\">hemodynamically unstable</span> patient, but this patient is stable. Additionally, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=in0JGg&anker=Zf22a2d04575027ccbd9bc2a111f58066\" data-learningcard-id=\"in0JGg\" data-anker=\"Zf22a2d04575027ccbd9bc2a111f58066\" data-sememe-id=\"eK0x2S\">x-ray</a> has low <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Z252fcd07b99eb21a8bff067bee67fd9d\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Z252fcd07b99eb21a8bff067bee67fd9d\" data-section-id=\"EfW8Lk0\" data-sememe-id=\"wkXhJy\">sensitivity</a> and cannot reliably visualize the obstruction, identify the underlying cause, or evaluate for complications.</div>",
